        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(models): keep generated secret refs out of plaintext",
        "body": "Fixes #88562.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Persist generated env-backed SecretRef provider auth as `secretref-env:<NAME>` instead of a bare env var name.\n- Resolve that marker through `process.env` at model registry request time.\n- Treat string SecretRef markers as audit-safe while still flagging unresolved object SecretRefs and true plaintext strings.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: Per-agent `models.json` generation could persist auth-profile env `keyRef` values as bare strings such as `TENSORIX_API_KEY`, which looked like plaintext to the deep security audit and produced false-positive `PLAINTEXT_FOUND` findings.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout at `/Users/andy/openclaw-88562`, branch `fix/models-json-secret-ref-88562`, commit `7215469a2f`.\n\nExact steps or command run after the patch:\n\n```text\nnode scripts/test-projects.mjs src/agents/models-config.applies-config-env-vars.test.ts src/agents/models-config.providers.auth-aliases.test.ts src/agents/models-config.providers.auth-provenance.test.ts src/agents/models-config.providers.cloudflare-ai-gateway.test.ts src/agents/models-config.providers.normalize-keys.test.ts src/agents/models-config.providers.vercel-ai-gateway.test.ts src/agents/models-config.runtime-source-snapshot.test.ts src/agents/sessions/model-registry.test.ts src/secrets/audit.test.ts src/agents/models-config.uses-first-github-copilot-profile-env-tokens.test.ts\npnpm check:test-types\nOPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=/tmp/openclaw-88562-proof-gBWm15 TENSORIX_API_KEY=redacted-test-token node --import tsx --input-type=module <security-audit-runtime-proof>\ngit log --format='%h %an <%ae> %s' upstream/main..HEAD\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  25 passed (25)\nTest Files  9 passed (9)\nTests  64 passed (64)\n[test] passed 2 Vitest shards in 22.58s\npnpm check:test-types: passed\n\nproof_state_dir=/tmp/openclaw-88562-proof-gBWm15\nmodels_apiKey=secretref-env:TENSORIX_API_KEY\nmodels_findings=[]\nplaintext_models_findings=0\n\n7b65e36716 Andy Ye <35905412+TurboTheTurtle@users.noreply.github.com> Fix models json secret ref api keys\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: A generated provider backed by an auth-profile env `keyRef` now gets `apiKey: \"secretref-env:TENSORIX_API_KEY\"`; the runtime resolver resolves that marker through `process.env.TENSORIX_API_KEY`, and the security audit runtime reports no `models.json` findings and zero `PLAINTEXT_FOUND` findings for that marker.\n\nWhat was not tested: The source-tree CLI wrapper requires built `dist/entry.(m)js`, so the proof invoked the patched security audit runtime directly from source rather than `node openclaw.mjs security audit --json`.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Maintainer can modify: enabled.\n\n",
